- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper describes a novel technique for instrumenting self-tracking of subjective experience using a wearable device, which is a human-computer interaction application. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of technology in psychotherapeutic treatment for PTSD, which has societal implications. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely as the paper does not involve any computational complexity analysis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also less likely as the paper does not involve any AI or machine learning techniques.
